Op-Ed article by Morgan Stanley economist Richard Berner warns that war against terrorism will impose long-term economic costs in form of higher insurance and security costs, maintenance of larger inventories and new Internet security measures; explains that spending more on defense will erase decade-long 'peace dividend' and crowd out other investments that helped transform budget deficits into surpluses. Full article available upon reasonable request. Security spend as calibrator • Corp budget for security: 3% for manufacturing...8% for banks • IT headcount for security: 5% of total • IT budget for security: 12% hardware 20% software 15% services 53% staff